        "turn": 1,
        "name": "Act 1",
        "intent": "[The hearing room gathers itself under a hard morning light; wet coats steam at the back wall, and the table waits with its ink, ledgers, and silence. Outside, the sea keeps striking below the windows.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 5,
        "name": "Act 2",
        "intent": "[The ledger stays open to the bearing, but the clerk's hand hovers short of the next line. The wet room has shed some of its certainty; what remains is the sound of weather and the empty place where a tower-name should be.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 9,
        "name": "Act 3",
        "intent": "[The room changes its posture: no longer a tribunal with a culprit, but an inquiry with an absence at its center. A constable is sent out into the weather, and the benches lean toward what the next physical thing may say.]"
      },
      {
        "turn": 16,
        "name": "Act 4",
        "intent": "[The book is closed, but the room does not release its breath. Beyond the windows the storm keeps working at the coast, and the next act enters with colder pressure: not a name on paper now, but movement through weather toward a place no one can leave abstract.]"
      }
    ],
